Spayed Female Domestic Shorthair Cat

Age: 17 YEARS 2 MONTHS

Hi! My name is Pepper and I am available for adoption. I was brought in by my previous owner on December 24, 2017 because I like getting attention on my own terms.

As one who is "advanced in years" I believe I have earned the right to be pet when I want and where I want. If you are petting me wrong or too much, I am not afraid to tell you to slow down, ya young whipper-snapper!

If you haven't already guessed, I have a bit of an attitude and I am completely fine with that. You don't get to be this spry at the age of 17 by being passive and boring!

I do enjoy being pet but there are some part of my body that are more sensitive with age - like my back and hind end - that I do not enjoy being touched. I would appreciate your respect and understanding and only pet me where I like to be pet. I will do best in an adult only home that is very cat savvy.

Don't be fooled by my double-digit age, I am still active and will fill your home with lots of conversation - I enjoy the sound of my own voice - and sassiness!

My personality color is RED. I am a spirited cat with a fun-loving personality! I may be sensitive to handling, so I would do best in a home with a cat savvy family who knows when to give me some space.

A veterinarian has diagnosed or tentatively diagnosed the above-described pet with the following condition(s):

1) This animal has moderate dental tartar and gingivitis. This may require a dental cleaning under anesthesia and potentially need x-rays or tooth extractions. Please follow up with your regular veterinarian to form the best treatment plan.

2) Geriatric animal- Pepper has mildly increased kidney values and early renal insufficiency is suspected. Please consult with you regular veterinarian for recommendations for ongoing care.

As a result of these conditions, your pet may need specialized care consisting of any or all of the below. Please note this is not intended to be an exhaustive list.

- Special diet or prescription foods

- Prescription or over-the-counter medicines

- Special skin care or shampoos

- Regular veterinarian visits, which may include blood tests or other monitoring

- Possible surgery or other procedures as determined by your veterinarian

Memo:
Received on: 2017-06-23

Description: Dilute Tor Spayed Female Domestic Longhair Cat

Age: 2 YEARS 8 MONTHS

Current Location: In RASKC Foster Home

I'm a unique little cat. I talk big game but I'm a sweet heart. I have some

feist to me, but once I get attached I'll follow you around everywhere,

show you love, curl up on you, and "meep" at you. I love joining you on the

couch, but I'll wait for an invitation first as I stare at you with wishful

eyes. I love being pet, and will greet you at the door every time you come

home. I like to play too. My temperament has improved so much, and my

pheromone collar makes me even more peaceable (but it's optional).

I'm picky about who I like, so it may take me a while for to trust someone.

It's a hit or miss on how I do with visitors (but still bring them), so

it's unlikely that I'll do well with kids. In general, I'd fit better in an

adults home where the owners know when to give me space. However, I don't

hold grudges, and I'll come back a few moments later sweet again. Even

though I love the sound of kittens on the computer, I'll hiss if you bring

actual pets into the house.

Dietary needs: Since I love food, I eat too quickly and need a special

"maze" bowl for dry food, otherwise I'll barf. Also, I need to be fed wet

food more often because I get chubby with dry food.

Due to my unique nature, I need a special, patient, and loving home who

will understand me and make me feel safe and loved. Because I was on the

street at some point, I feel threatened more easily (hence hiss), but I

think my "cat therapy" is slowly healing me :) Due to my history, the top

of one ear is also cut off to mark me as spayed.

Please note that I tested positive for FeLV with the ELISA test, which

means I may or may not develop the actual disease. The IFA is the only

confirmatory test. I'm so glad FeLV saved me from being a barn cat and gave

me the chance at having a loving home!

All I want is a good, loving home!

Adoption Fee: $30.00

Description: Black Spayed Female Domestic Longhair Cat

Age: 11 YEARS 4 MONTHS

Current Location: In RASKC Foster Home

This is my friend Gertie. She is an 11-year-old adoptable cat currently living in a foster home. Unlike most fosters she's not in care because of her age or her health, but because of her attitude. When she first came to the shelter she was hissy and snarly and very difficult to manage. Ordinarily a cat that unfriendly to humans would be put up for adoption as a barn cat, but Gertie is front declawed and would never be able to defend herself outdoors. Her only hope was to get away from the stress of the shelter environment to see if some loving care could bring her back to the light side.

After months in foster care Gertie is a changed cat. Granted, she's still something of a curmudgeon and has definite opinions about how things ought to be, but she enjoys petting and brushing, and has a rumbling purr that she's happy to share. She is more than ready to go to her forever home, ideally where she can rule over her own private space. Gertie needs an adopter who is willing to learn her signals and respect her limits, and who appreciates that winning the heart of a "difficult" animal is well worth the patience it will require. Please contact Melodye Johnson - melodyej63@msn.com or (253)740-0269 (ok to text)
